        "row_nddzfW": {
          "type": "row",
          "settings": {
            "content-title": "Why goalkeeper gloves wear out",
            "content-description": "<p class=\"section-content__text\">Soft latex = elite grip.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">But soft latex also means more wear.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">The better the grip, the more sensitive the glove. Match latex is designed to perform, not to take endless punishment. That’s why how you treat your gloves — and how you dive — matters.</p>",
            "content-image": "shopify://shop_images/goalkeeper_goalie_goalkeepergloves_goaliegloves_wornout_newglovesplease_100gloves_thehundredglove_wontletmethrowthemaway.jpg",
            "content-isadaptive": false
          }
        },
        "row_FwVqXA": {
          "type": "row",
          "settings": {
            "content-title": "Your Technique Matters (Especially for Younger Keepers)",
            "content-description": "<p class=\"section-content__text\">Let’s be blunt: most glove damage doesn’t come from dodgy manufacturing.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">It comes from bad habits.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">If you’re punching the ground every dive, scraping your hands on turf, dragging your palms when you get up — your gloves will fall apart fast. We see it all the time, especially with junior keepers who are still learning how to land, push off, and move correctly.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">It’s not always the glove. Sometimes it’s the goalkeeper.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">Great technique = longer glove lifespan.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">Clean handling, smart recovery, and controlled movement all reduce wear.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">It’s not about babying your gloves — it’s about not battering them needlessly.</p>",
            "content-image": "shopify://shop_images/MPH-02561.jpg",
            "content-isadaptive": false
          }
        },
        "row_KzRAUd": {
          "type": "row",
          "settings": {
            "content-title": "How to make your gloves last longer",
            "content-description": "<ol class=\"section-content__list\">\n<li class=\"section-content__elem\">Rinse after every session<br>Use cold or lukewarm water — no soap. Gently rinse out dirt and sweat. Every session means every session.\n</li>\n<li class=\"section-content__elem\">Air dry only<br>No radiators. No hairdryers. No sun. Heat kills latex.<br>Dry them flat in a cool, shaded room.</li>\n<li class=\"section-content__elem\">Use separate gloves for training and matches<br>Train hard. Play harder. But don’t wear the same pair for both.<br>One training pair. One match pair. Simple.</li>\n<li class=\"section-content__elem\">Store them properly<br>Never leave gloves bunched up in your bag. Store them flat, palms together, in a glove wallet or breathable bag.</li>\n<li class=\"section-content__elem\">Activate the grip before play<br>Lightly dampen the palms with clean water before kick-off.<br>Moist latex = more grip, less abrasion, and a longer life.</li>\n</ol>",
            "content-image": "shopify://shop_images/MPH01404.jpg",
            "content-isadaptive": true
          }
        }
      },
